👉🏿New Dreamsaber with classic, OG style 10mm and custom fitted Cedar case. 
I used beautiful local Oregon grown Red Cedar. 🌲This one has a stainless steel Star Tetrahedron (Metatrons cube) inlaid in the top of the box. ⚙️ Metatron’s Cube starts with the Flower of Life shape, and connects all 13 circles with straight lines. Metatron’s Cube includes all 5 Platonic Solids hidden inside, symbolizing the underlying geometric patterns found throughout our universe. It’s named after Archangel Metatron, who watches over the flow of energy in creation and provides a connection to the divine. Metatron’s Cube is balanced and provides a visual focal point for meditation. It can replace negative thoughts with positive ones. 
I really like the way these new boxes are coming out and I am proud to share them with you!

Balance is key. 
How shall we measure success?
It isn’t popularity, money, or awards from critical people. Success occurs in the privacy of the soul. It comes before you decide to show it to anyone. 

Success has nothing to do with outside variables. 
This is the essence of great art.  To make it for no other purpose than creating our own version of the beautiful, bringing all of ourselves to every project. To be aware. We do the best, as we see the best; with our own vision and taste. No one else. 
Measurements of greatness is subjective, like the art itself. There is no hard metric. We are performing for an audience of one. 
Thanks for checking it out.
This has been a public service announcement. For anyone who needs it. 
Now go be yourself and make art!

I’ve been playing around with scale lately . The top lightsaber is hollow and it’s exactly 1/3 scale of my full size ones and it’s functional! (Dry pipe with bowl in pommel) The lower one is solid and it’s exactly 1/4 scale. Im finding it’s an advantage to be able to design and build on a smaller scale and play around with proportions and colors before I scale up to full size functional recyclers. This helps to get everything dialed in and the proportions correct moving forward. Hope you all have a great day! 🔥❤️ #dreamfireglass

This one is coming along. The metal work takes a lot of patience. I’m learning as I go.
It has a couple of layers of copper so far. 
Making art; it’s a living. It’s honest. It’s ok.
Humble. Just try to enjoy my time. Everyday. 
There’s no such thing as getting ahead in life. It’s all just…. You can’t take it with you. 
What do you want?
There’s no easy money in glass anymore.
Doesn’t matter.
If it’s too easy. It’s boring
It’s about survival. Now.
Just make more than you spend.
Main fear is being cringe. Perception. Don’t want people to feel sorry for me.
Just do your best and that’s all. 
Do what you want.
Don’t worry about if they like or not. 
Can’t control it.

Money is meaningless anyways 
It got to be about more than numbers. 
Maybe it’s good to be underdog
Maybe it doesn’t matter 
Who really cares?

It’s a spiritual pursuit.
Faith
Trust in faith
That it will. 
Eventually 
All work out in the end.
#metalwork

This one is very special. Last summer, I asked my wife if she could help me create an ultimate space case. My Michelle spent over two months, countless hours working on this space Crystal saber case. Using glass and resin, along with some magic dust; She made something that looks like it came from outer space; It came out amazing!!🔥
We’ve been together for 29 years. It is our first collab together in a long while. (We used to make glass pieces together back in the day.)
